Class SlyceUIParams

  • java.lang.Object
    • it.slyce.sdk.ui.SlyceUIParams

  • public final class SlyceUIParams
extends java.lang.Object
    Convenience class for packaging parameters that need to be passed to UI mode (e.g., SlyceActivity and SlyceFragment.

      • getLensIdsWithFallback

        public java.util.List<java.lang.String> getLensIdsWithFallback()
        Gets a list of lens IDs. Note that if no lens IDs have been provided, this will fallback to returning a list of all lens IDs provided via the account configuration. This was initially done to provide backwards compatibility with clients who launching UI mode with a list of lens IDs instead of a mode. All of those are deprecated, and once removed, we can make this only return the list of lens IDs provided via the account configuration.
        Returns:
        a list of lens IDs.
